    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect DFT output indexing and loop bounds in dft6144 implementation\n\n### Summary\nThe 6144-point DFT (dft6144) and inverse DFT (idft6144) functions in oai_dfts.c had multiple critical bugs causing incorrect FFT computation and potential buffer overflows. The functions were reading twice the input data they should and writing output to incorrect memory locations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Fixed input splitting loop bounds in both dft6144 and idft6144 from 2048 iterations to 1024 iterations\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Corrected butterfly combination loop bounds from i<4096 to i<6144\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Fixed output indexing from (output+i, output+4096+i, output+8192+i) to (output+i, output+2048+i, output+4096+i)\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Adjusted scaling loop iterations from 96 to 384 to process all 6144 output elements\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running 5G NR gNB with 6144-point DFT processing enabled, users may observe:\n- Incorrect channel estimation and signal processing results\n- Buffer overflows causing segmentation faults during DFT operations\n- Memory corruption leading to unpredictable behavior in PHY layer processing\n- Mismatch between expected and actual FFT output values when debugging DFT outputs\n\nThe issue manifests when processing 6144-sample inputs through the radix-3 decomposition DFT implementation, particularly in high bandwidth NR configurations using 6144-point FFTs.\n"
}